    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-06-18T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-06-18T10:00:00-05:00" n="298"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d298">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">862.51/4062: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berne</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-06-18T16:00:00+01:00"
                            >June 18, 1934—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 18—12:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>18. I am informed by Swiss Department of Commerce official that an agreement with
                    the German Government was reached on June 16 providing that payments into the
                    Swiss “special account” with the Reichsbank which were suspended on June 9 are
                    now resumed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
